Thank You, Body, for giving me the vessel to enjoy life, friendship (and too much tequila), now let's get you some energy!

It is never too late 💞

You are not too old, too busy, too broken, too far gone, too anything. You are worthy and deserving every day, forever.
 
Not sure where to start? Feel like a fraud? I get it! I had given up on myself at one point, too. But let's break this down into simpler terms:
 
When you start anything new (school, job, relationship, hobby, etc), you are not instantly good at it. But you still show up on day one with whatever skills and knowledge you have, ready to try your best and learn to do better.
 
Practicing self-love and building new habits is the same technique. Start small and slow. Bring to the table what you already know about yourself and self care, and then slowly build on those things as you connect to yourself and discover your unique needs. There is no wrong way to do this, and you are the only authority on what you need to feel happy and healthy.
 
If you're still having a hard time discovering your most basic needs, then talk to someone about gaining the tools to get to know yourself in this way. This is gifting yourself the knowledge and power that you will be able to use every day for the rest of your life. This step alone is one of the biggest acts of self-love one could ever do for themselves.
 
I know just the person for you to talk to.. it's me 😘 DM me for private coaching details!
.
.

.

Fitness is for EVERYBODY and EVERY BODY!
 
Fitness doesn't have a size or a shape. It doesn't discriminate or judge. It doesn't shame or critique.
 
Fitness doesn't do those things. People do.
 
Insecure people that have their own messed up views on their own bodies because of the environment they grew up in and the experiences they've had that have shaped their views on bodies and worth.
 
My wish for those people (and everyone) is that they find the freedom of body appreciation and realize that EVERY BODY is a gift.
 
You don't return a gift because of the way it's wrapped. You cherish what's inside. 🎁
.
.

Tips for loving yourself:
                 
Guess what? You already do.
                 
Maybe you just don't know how to show it yet.
                 
Hear me out real quick even if you just rolled your eyes because you don't believe it to be true for you.
                  
If there has ever been a time where you tried to better your life in any way (health, education, career, relationships, etc.) then you love yourself.
                 
If you have ever sought out help or solutions to a problem you were having then you love yourself.
                 
If you have ever even wished for a better life for yourself, then you love yourself and want the best for yourself.
                 
What I'm trying to say is that deep inside you have always loved yourself but life is hard sometimes and society has a funny way of making you forget that self-love.
                 
NEW CAPTION: How to remember that you love yourself through loving actions.
                 
1️⃣ eat delicious foods that energize you
2️⃣ move your body in enjoyable ways
3️⃣ have an attitude of gratitude
(love what is already in your life)
4️⃣ give yourself the gift of grace and human error
(you're not a robot)
5️⃣ choose positivity as much as possible
(people, thoughts, environment)
                 
Which number 1-5 could you use a little more of in your life right now?

"But if I stop dieting, I might gain weight."
 
There is always a possibility of your body weight shifting either way so I can't say for sure what will happen when you choose to leave diet culture and come home to yourself.
 
What I can say for sure is that you'll gain:
 
- SELF-CONNECTION: made when you stop outsourcing your own unique needs and learn self trust.
- PURPOSE: lean into what lights you up without carrying outside judgement.
- FREEDOM: be YOU and be free from society's opinions on how you should live your life.
- INNER PEACE: be at peace with yourself, mind body & soul.
- HEALING, HAPPINESS, MEMORIES, EXPERIENCES: all things that have been put on the back burner for diet culture. 
 
It's time to ask yourself what's more important to you at this time? Losing or gaining?
 
Want to leave diet culture behind but not sure where to start? Schedule a discovery session with me and take a dive into what your world will look like without diets..(spoiler alert: it's fking awesome!🎉) DM me for details!

When I had a smaller body I would get so much praise about my physical appearance and yes.. I enjoyed it.
 
Gaining weight and hearing crickets now has really confirmed every fear that I grew up with, knowing that a bigger body is not a desired body in society. Thankfully, the body appreciation work I've done helps me know that's not my problem.
 
It has also helped me weed out the people in my life that have body biases that I cannot do anything about. I do not miss people that would constantly ask me what I ate in a day. I do not miss people that marveled in my weight loss. I do not miss people that thought I was "brave" for wearing a crop top without having a flat belly.
 
I miss the attention because I'm a human being that deserves attention. But I rejoice in the peace that I have in my body and the people in my life that celebrate me at any size. 🕊
.
.
.

It can be different starting with you.
 
 
My intuitive living program Body Appreciation Blueprint is centered around exactly this, finally breaking free from the diet culture damage that's been passed down through generations. It ends with us.
